##Import data

data_dir<-"/media/user/seagate_ICM/AICDA_analysis/Github_repository/" #Set to where you downloaded the data
setwd(data_dir)
source('r/prerequisites.R')

data2<-as.data.frame(read.delim("Data/Figure1/Cohorts_figure1A.tab",colClasses = c("factor","factor","numeric","factor","numeric","numeric","numeric","numeric")))

#
# Set a number of 'empty bar' to add at the end of each Cohort
empty_bar=2
nObsType=5 #Set as number of divisions wanted for plotting (eg. 10%, 20%....100%)
data2$Cohort<-as.factor(data2$Cohort)
data2$Cohort <- factor(data2$Cohort,levels=c("ICGC","TCGA","ICI","Riaz et al","Hematological","Pediatric","Composite"))
data2$Subgroup <- factor(data2$Subgroup,levels=c("ICGC","TCGA","MSKCC-IMPACT","Pender et al","Miao et al","Braun et al","Liu et al","Hugo et al","Riaz et al","Hematological","Pediatric","Composite"))
data2$Tumor_type<-factor(data2$Tumor_type,levels=names(table(data2$Tumor_type)))


# Get the name and the y position of each label for each bar
label_data= data2 %>% group_by(id, Tumor_type) %>% dplyr::summarize(tot=sum(n_corrected),Samples=total)
label_data$lab<-paste0(label_data$Tumor_type,"(n=",label_data$Samples,")")
 label_data<-label_data[!duplicated(label_data$id),]
number_of_bar=nrow(label_data)
angle= 90 - 360 * (label_data$id-0.5) /number_of_bar     # I substract 0.5 because the letter must have the angle of the center of the bars. Not extreme right(1) or extreme left (0)
label_data$hjust<-ifelse( angle < -90, 1, 0)
label_data$angle<-ifelse(angle < -90, angle+180, angle)

 
 
# prepare a data frame for base lines, to nae the cohorts
base_data=data2 %>% 
  group_by(Cohort) %>% 
  dplyr::summarize(start=min(id), end=max(id) - empty_bar) %>% 
  dplyr::rowwise() %>% 
  dplyr::mutate(title=mean(c(start, end)))
 

# prepare a data frame for grid (scales)
grid_data = base_data
grid_data$end = grid_data$end[ c( nrow(grid_data), 1:nrow(grid_data)-1)] + 1
grid_data$start = grid_data$start - 1
grid_data$end =grid_data$end +.5
grid_data$start =grid_data$start +.5
grid_data=grid_data[-1,]

 ###Edit for lines of cohorts...
base_data$start<-base_data$start+.5
base_data$end<-base_data$end+.5
##
base_data$lab<-paste0(base_data$Cohort,"\nn=",c("2775","9264","2261","68","3859","1051","31353"))
##
base_data_lines<-base_data
base_data_lines$start[]<-base_data_lines$start[]-1;base_data_lines$end[]<-base_data_lines$end[]+1

pie_dat

##
p_signatures_semideconv_icgc<-list();total_n_icgc<-rep(1,35)
for (i in 1:35) {
  order<-NULL
  if (is.null(SBS_signatures_exp_pancancer_NO_AICDA_icgc[[i]]$sig_props$AICDA_canonical)=="FALSE") {
    order<-order(colSums(t(SBS_signatures_exp_pancancer_NO_AICDA_icgc[[i]]$sig_props$AICDA_canonical)), decreasing = T)#Order according to highest AICDA canonical proportion (if present)
  }
  order_sigs<-colnames(SBS_signatures_exp_pancancer_NO_AICDA_icgc[[i]]$sig_props)
  if (is.null(SBS_signatures_exp_pancancer_NO_AICDA_icgc[[i]]$sig_props$SBS9)=="FALSE") {
    order_sigs<-  order_sigs[c(which(order_sigs!="SBS9"),which(order_sigs=="SBS9"))]
  }#Put AICDA and SBS9 together (if present)
  if (is.null(SBS_signatures_exp_pancancer_NO_AICDA_icgc[[i]]$sig_props$AICDA_canonical)=="FALSE") {
    order_sigs<-order_sigs[c(which(order_sigs!="AICDA_canonical"),which(order_sigs=="AICDA_canonical"))]
  }
  p_signatures_semideconv_icgc[[i]]<-signature_exposure_plot2(regression_line = "AICDA_canonical",order = order,signature_colours = sig_cols,mutSign_nums =   SBS_signatures_exp_pancancer_NO_AICDA_icgc[[i]]$sig_nums[,order_sigs],mutSign_props =SBS_signatures_exp_pancancer_NO_AICDA_icgc[[i]]$sig_props[,order_sigs] )+ ggtitle(paste0("Mutational Signature exposure in ",names(SBS_signatures_exp_pancancer_NO_AICDA_icgc[i])," (n = ",nrow(SBS_signatures_exp_pancancer_NO_AICDA_icgc[[i]]$sig_nums),")"))+theme(axis.text.x=element_blank())+xlab(paste0(names(SBS_signatures_exp_pancancer_NO_AICDA_icgc[i])," (n = ",nrow(SBS_signatures_exp_pancancer_NO_AICDA_icgc[[i]]$sig_nums),")")) #Remove samples names
  total_n_icgc[i]<-nrow(SBS_signatures_exp_pancancer_NO_AICDA_icgc[[i]]$sig_nums)
}
names(total_n_icgc)<-icgc_tumorType
